  "prompt": "How is Josh Elliott doing at NBC Sports? Was it a smart move for him to leave Good Morning America?",
  "response": "Josh Elliott joined NBC Sports in 2016 after leaving CBS News, not Good Morning America (GMA). He left GMA in 2014 to join CBS News. \n\nAt NBC Sports, Elliott has worked as a host and play-by-play commentator. He has covered various sports events, including the Olympic Games and the NFL. His role at NBC Sports has allowed him to focus more on sports, which aligns with his background and interests.\n\nRegarding whether it was a smart move to leave GMA, opinions vary. When Elliott left GMA in 2014, it was reported that he was seeking a higher salary and a more prominent role, which he felt he could achieve at CBS News. However, his time at CBS was relatively short-lived, as he was let go in 2016.\n\nIn hindsight, moving to CBS might not have been the best decision for his career trajectory, as it did not lead to long-term stability. However, his subsequent move to NBC Sports allowed him to return to a field he was passionate about and had experience in, which could be seen as a positive step.\n\nUltimately, the decision to leave GMA and the subsequent moves to CBS and NBC Sports have had mixed results. While it did not lead to the long-term success he might have hoped for at CBS, his current role at NBC Sports seems to be a good fit for his skills and interests.",
